						               													<description>S-Tris is 2-player game that combines tile laying like Blokus with the use of cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Before play starts, players modify the usable part of the board by putting some blocks anywhere on the board. Each players is dealt a certain number of cards, depending on the amount of players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On his turn a player plays a card, either a square or a helper card. In case of a square card he puts the corresponding piece on the board as long as it fits somewhere. In case of a helper card he carries out the special function. Some cards, like The Bomb, allow you to remove a piece first for instance.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player who gets rid of his cards first or with the least points on his cards left after all players have passed on their turn, wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
